{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>The synaptonemal complex (SC) is a tripartite structure that physically links homologous chromosomes during prophase I. The SC has a zipper-like structure composed of two lateral elements (LEs)  and a central element (CE). Transverse filaments, composed of SYCP1 molecules, bridge the gap between one LE and the CE.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Syce2/CESC1 localises to the CE and interacts with the transverse filament protein SYCP1.  Its localization to the CE is dependent on recruitment by SYCP1 [[cite:PUB00061629]].  Syce2/ CESC1 is required for synaptonemal complex assembly and also for double strand break repair and homologous recombination [[cite:PUB00083780]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR28398" "SYNAPTONEMAL COMPLEX CENTRAL ELEMENT PROTEIN 2"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Synaptonemal complex central element protein 2", "short" "Syce2"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 2, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 455, "taxa" 1791, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 732, "sets" 0, "proteins" 732, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 461}, "pathways" 1}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR034609", :literature {"PUB00061629" {"URL" nil, "issue" "Pt 12", "authors" ["Costa Y" "Speed R" "Ollinger R" "Alsheimer M" "Semple CA" "Gautier P" "Maratou K" "Novak I" "Hoog C" "Benavente R" "Cooke HJ."], "ISO_journal" "J. Cell. Sci.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1242/jcs.02402", "medline_journal" "J Cell Sci", "title" "Two novel proteins recruited by synaptonemal complex protein 1 (SYCP1) are at the centre of meiosis.", "year" 2005, "raw_pages" "2755-62", "volume" "118", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 15944401}, "PUB00083780" {"URL" nil, "issue" "6", "authors" ["Bolcun-Filas E" "Costa Y" "Speed R" "Taggart M" "Benavente R" "De Roo